Open Redirect Severity: High Open redirection vulnerabilities arise when an application incorporates user-controllable data into a redirection target in an unsafe way. An attacker can construct a URL within the application that causes a redirection to an arbitrary external domain. Session Hijacking Using an open-redirect vulnerability, it is possible to steal the application user's sensitive cookie. Specifically, the access_token and id_token cookies. These two cookies will allow an attacker to interact with the application's GraphQL scheme as the victim.
